        THERE ARE THREE DD CARDS WHICH ARE REQUIRED TO EXECUTE SMART.  T
   ARE SYSUT1, SYSUT2, AND SYSUT3.  SYSUT1  IS THE INPUT DATASET CONTAIN
   THE RAW TEXT. SYSUT2 IS THE OUTPUT DATASET CONTAINING THE OUTPUT REPO
   THE  DEFAULT DCB  ATTRIBUTES FOR  SYSUT2 IS  RECFM=FBA BLKSIZE=1330
   LRECL=133 UNLESS PARM OPTION L IS SPECIFIED, THEN THE DEFAULT ATTRIBU
   ARE  RECFM=FBA LRECL=80  AND BLKSIZE=3120.  YOU CAN  OVERRIDE THESE
   ATTRIBUTES  BY SPECIFYING THE DCB INFORMATION ON THE JCL DDCARD.  IF
   OMIT SOME INFORMATION, THE DEFAULT VALUE(S) WILL BE USED. IF YOU WISH
   OUTPUT THE MANUAL TO A DATASET, YOU CAN POINT THE SYSUT2 DD CARD TO T
   DATASET AND SMART WILL USE ITS DCB ATTRIBUTES. SYSUT3 IS A WORK DATAS
   BELOW  IS A SAMPLE JCL STREAM  WHICH CAN BE USED  TO CREATE THIS MANU

